A Special Note on ado and bluebird
When using agency copilot or agency claude in an Azure DevOps repository, these MCP servers are configured automatically:

bluebird — Engineering Copilot / Bluebird is included by default. It allows engineers to understand large, complex codebases, improve them faster, and enhance development work.

ado — The Azure DevOps MCP server auto-detects your organization from the git remote. You can override this with --mcp 'ado --organization myorg' or by configuring it explicitly in a config file.

To reduce tool surface and context size, you can narrow ADO to specific toolsets via --toolsets (for example, --toolsets core,repositories,pipelines,search). The same option is available in agency.toml / agency.yaml using toolsets.

Bluebird Authentication in Managed Identity Pipelines
In pipeline environments, Bluebird authenticates using SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN by default. However, if your pipeline overrides SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN with a managed identity token (e.g., to access a cross-org repo), this conflicts with the ADO MCP's OIDC flow, which also reads SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN.

To resolve this, set AGENCY_BLUEBIRD_AUTH_TOKEN with the managed identity token. Bluebird will use it instead of SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN, leaving the original pipeline token available for the ADO MCP's OIDC authentication.

Token resolution priority for Bluebird (stdio/pipeline mode):

AGENCY_BLUEBIRD_AUTH_TOKEN (explicit override)
SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN (pipeline default)
azureauth interactive flow (local dev only)
Logger MCP
The Logger MCP provides agents with two capabilities: emitting custom events to Application Insights and reading/writing files in a sandboxed per-session directory.

Tools
Tool	Description
log_event	Emit a custom event to Application Insights with an arbitrary JSON payload. The session_id is injected authoritatively and cannot be overridden.
write_file	Write a UTF-8 file inside the logger sandbox. Parent directories are created automatically.
read_file	Read a UTF-8 file from the logger sandbox (up to 1 MiB by default).
list_files	List files in the sandbox (optionally recursive).
copy_file	Copy any on-disk file into the sandbox. The source path is unrestricted; only the destination must be sandbox-relative.
Configuration
Option	Default	Description
--connection-string	AGENCY_LOGGER_APPINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING env var	Application Insights connection string for log_event. Individual calls may override this per-call.
--filestore-dir-name	agency_mcp_logger_files	Name of the sandbox directory created under the Agency log folder.
Usage
# Enable for a session
agency copilot --mcp logger

# With a specific connection string
agency copilot --mcp "logger --connection-string InstrumentationKey=..."

# Add to Agency config
agency config set --mcp logger
Security Model
session_id enforcement: The MCP injects the authoritative session ID from AGENCY_SESSION_ID into every log_event call. Any caller-supplied session_id or agency.*/agency_ prefixed attributes are stripped before emission.
Sandbox safety: All file paths (write_file, read_file, list_files, copy_file destination) are validated to prevent path traversal — .., absolute paths, Windows UNC paths, drive-relative paths, alternate data streams, and reserved device names (CON, PRN, etc.) are all rejected.
copy_file source: The copy_file source parameter accepts any path the process can read. This mirrors the filesystem access the calling agent already has — it is a staging convenience, not a new privilege boundary.
Using Agency MCPs with Claude Code Directly
If you're using Claude Code directly (not via agency claude), you can add Agency MCP servers manually:

# Azure DevOps
claude mcp add --transport stdio ado -- agency mcp ado

# Bluebird
claude mcp add --transport stdio bluebird -- agency mcp bluebird

# Bluebird mini mode
claude mcp add --transport stdio bluebird -- agency mcp bluebird --mini

# WorkIQ (M365 Copilot)
claude mcp add --transport stdio workiq -- agency mcp workiq

# Security Context
claude mcp add --transport stdio security-context -- agency mcp security-context

# Microsoft Teams
claude mcp add --transport stdio teams -- agency mcp teams

# Microsoft Mail
claude mcp add --transport stdio mail -- agency mcp mail

# Microsoft Calendar
claude mcp add --transport stdio calendar -- agency mcp calendar

# CloudBuild
claude mcp add --transport stdio cloudbuild -- agency mcp cloudbuild

# Microsoft Word
claude mcp add --transport stdio word -- agency mcp word

# Microsoft Planner
claude mcp add --transport stdio planner -- agency mcp planner

# M365 User (Graph user details, manager, team, reports)
claude mcp add --transport stdio m365-user -- agency mcp m365-user

# M365 Copilot (search across M365 content)
claude mcp add --transport stdio m365-copilot -- agency mcp m365-copilot

# Logger (App Insights events and sandboxed file storage)
claude mcp add --transport stdio logger -- agency mcp logger